Over 30 Nollywood movie stars among other dignitaries from  different sectors gathered at the Sky Cinemas, Sangotedo on Sunday, August 25 for the premiere of Chika Lann’s production, ‘The Millions’. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1247599" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=640%2C427&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?resize=560%2C373&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Million.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Ramsey Nouah, Broda Shagi, Shirley Ann, Ayo Makun, Nancy Isime, Ernest Obi, Anthony Monjaro, Judith Audu, Ali Nuhu, Tchidi Chikere and a host of others, dressed like Millionaire Gangsters gathered to watch for the first time the most talked about movie of the season, ‘The Millions’. The hall could not contain the cheers, laughter, excitement and the fulfillment that comes from seeing the biggest heist movie Nollywood has ever produced. Everyone agrees that all the actors brought their A-Game. Advance screenings for ‘The Millions’ took place at Viva Cinemas and Cartege Cinemas from Wednesday, August 28. Ayo Makun (AY) hosted ‘Meet and Greet’ with fans who have come out to see the movie on the release date, August 30, 2019. Ramsey Nouah, Broda Shaggi and other stars  also were in cinemas across the country on the opening weekend for ‘Meet and Greet’ with fans. It was the gathering of stars at the weekend as over 30 Nollywood actors, among other dignitaries from different sectors gathered for the premiere of the most talked about movie of the season, ‘ The Millions’. August 28, 2019 In "Entertainment" AY’s 30 Days in Atlanta, which hit the cinemas yesterday startled theatre buffs when it carted away four awards at the just concluded Golden Icons Academy Movie Awards (GIAMA) which took place in Houston Texas last Saturday. November 1, 2014 In "Entertainment" 30 days in Atlanta, a movie by popular stand-up comedian, Ayo Makun, aka AY, has made it into the Guinness Book of World Records. According to AY, the movie which featured top actors, Ramsey Noah, Richard Mofe Damijo, Desmond Elliot, Princess Chineke, Majid Michael and a host of others, was… September 9, 2016 In "Entertainment"